name: 17 min from City Center, 50 sqm, Free Parking
description:
Oktoberfest is close enough to get there in about ten minutes. But it is far enough to avoid myriads of drunk Oktoberfest people when you want to spend a quiet night. To get ready for a new day, enjoy a cosy environment that feels like home.
Why not having your morning coffee on a beautiful balcony or veranda overlooking garden and park?
neighborhood_overview:
Just a few steps from the house there is a butcher, a bakery, two cafés, and a comprehensive set of deli markets and drugstores, including a vast choice of fresh organic food. A few minutes walk away there is a bank, post office, car rental, fitness studios, doctors and restaurants – and last but not least: one of Munichs biggest and most traditional Beergardens, where you can experience true Bavarian lifestyle all year round, just two metro-stops away from Oktoberfest...
This apartment is in a quiet green neighbourhood, but very well connected to various public transports and to major freeways and Autobahns. Transportation to the very city center and to fabulous Schwabing night life is around 15 min by public transport around the clock.
You also can enjoy one of the most beautiful and traditional beergardens in Munich, 5 min on foot away. There are restaurants, deli shops, supermarkets, bakery, butcher from 50 meters to 200 meters away.
Don't miss Westpark with its fab
host_about:
I feel as a local and an international citizen at the same time. I love meeting people from all over the world, I love travelling. And I love to share my personal favorites in and around Munich. For all those who want to get in touch with Munich lifestyle, little escapes into nature, good food - don't hesitate to ask me!
Lean back and feel welcome!

name: MUNICH OKTOBERFEST 2 rooms 4 people
description:
I have 2 rooms within my house for rent.

--> not the whole house is for rent, only the 2 guestrooms with shared facilities , which I use as well (kitchen, bathroom,..). Well... I live there, too. ;)

-- Both rooms have 2 queensize beds, very comfy for a good, quiet sleep.
-- shared, big bathroom and a additional restroom in the basement
-- daylight windows
-- towels, shower gel + shampoo provided
-- coffee, tea, water-boiler as well.
neighborhood_overview:
Quiet, green and cozy neigborhood.
Only 20-25min to the centre of Munich.
Full access to Metro, underground and Bus system.
host_about:
Hi there!  I have been a traveller / backpacker myself for many, many years-- and still are.
Therefore I know what is important for you as a traveller: a clean and safe neighborhood, a nice room with comfortable beds, easy and cheap transportation to the city centre or the major attractions...  and of course:  free Internet ;) 
As a host I can and want to provide you that. Our rooms are clean, spacious and lockable. Everyone gets a room and a house key, the area is silent and beautiful. No traffic, no sirens, no noise, .. just what you need for a recharching, quiet night. And in the morning:  free coffee (or tea ;) !
And of course:  free Internet!

Well...  I am an easy to handle person who likes to travel the world. If you need something, maybe just some information-- I am happy to help you. 
As a host I want you to feel welcome and leave with a nice impression of Munich, Bavaria, Germany and it´s people...    

I´m sure you gonna like it...  ;)

description:
Our apartment garuantees an exclusive Munich experience. Located in one of the best parts of town.
The neighborhood offers a variety of restaurants, clubs, outdoor and cultural activities. Public transportation is within 5 minutes walk.

neighborhood_overview:
Munich Schwabing is a burrough rich with history and the arts. The biggest city parks Englischer Garten and Olympia Park are within 15 minutes walking distance and provide great outdoor oportunities, beer gardens, swimming, fitness and more etc.

Publich transport is close by, all major subway and bus/tram lines are within 5-10 minutes walk. You can get to almost any location in town within about 30 minutes.

The neighborhood is full of diverse restaurants and coffeshops, from asian to italian to ethiopian to bavarian cuisine.

10 minutes walking distance is one of Munichs nightlife hot spots (Leopoldstrasse) with clubs, bars, more restaurants, cinemas and theaters.

The burrough (as all of Munich) is extremely safe around the clock.

In case of a medical emergency, hospitals are within 15-20 minutes walking distance.

description: The apartment is close to the park and not far from Leopoldstraße, cafes, restaurants & small shops  are right around the corner. Two minutes to the subway, bus & tram, which quickly lead to the city center in 5 minutes.
neighborhood_overview: I like the atmosphere here in this part of Munich. You only go out to the front door and see you right in life, with cafes, various international restaurants. The whole thing has a 'community' character. Various bakeries, kiosks and a very diverse Asia shop are around the corner. And don't forget, Schwabing is known for having a hairdresser on practically every corner in case you ever need one. Recently there are also spas, wellness & massage and of course the Nordbad with sauna...and it is only a few minutes to the fantastic Luitpoldpark...with joggers, bikers, walkers, football, or simply people who enjoy nature - and there is also a great beer garden with restaurant here. host_about: I am a passionate gardener & nature girl, enjoy winter camping at the seaside but warm weather as well. I fancy a good meal, love cooking and trying out recipes from other cultures. Reading a book is just as relaxing as well. I grow my  vegetables, fruits and herbs in my garden at home near Stuttgart, where I spend my weekends. I am a WE commuter to my little family with  2 kids and a lovely husband. My apartment  in Munich is centrally located, with nice parks in walking distance,  the park round the corner leads to the Olympic Park and its a nice walk to the English Garden as well. Although having a hunch for nature, I definitely need a clean apartment to feel 'home' and comfortable.

neighborhood_overview: In the nice and famous neighborhood "Schwabing" close to olympic park. Make sure to visit "Väterchen Timofei's" legacy there! He was a russian (!) hermit building a chapel, his house and even a small church from the debris of houses destroyed in WW II. The debris-hill is now called "Olympiaberg". When the Olympics were held in Munich his house and the chapel were about to be destroyed but the citizens of Munich fighted for his right to stay and the olympic facilities were planned to be built more to the north. He died aged 110 (his age was never verified) in 2004. Look it up on Wikipedia (Timofei Wassiljewitsch Prochorow)!

description:
Beautiful old building apartment, 4 rooms, in a great location in the central, beautiful, quiet district of Haidhausen. 3 bedrooms each with 1 double bed. Comfortable for 6 guests, 9 guests possible.
1 minute walk: Weissenburger Platz with fountain and flowers; 2 minutes: Rosenheimer Platz.: Tram, all S-Bahn; 8 minutes: Ostbahnhof by subway to the Oktoberfest; 10 minutes: Isarstrand for swimming, two beer gardens, Müllerchen Volksbad (Art Nouveau); 15 minutes: Eastern English Garden; 0-10 minutes: good restaurants.
neighborhood_overview: Haidhausen is a very popular neighborhood in Munich. There are all kinds of shops and lots of restaurants, from the easiest kebude to starred restaurant, according to Guide Michelin. It is a quiet and peaceful neighborhood adjacent to the river Isar. I find it very nice to walk by the river and in the summer you can even swim. In just 15-20 minutes you can walk to the city center (Marienplatz). The neighborhood offers a special mix of larger pompous skins and very small houses that are a bit atypical for a big city. This makes the neighborhood beautiful, special and cozy in a private mix.
host_about:
I'm a Swedish guy working for my own 3D CAD company in the city centre of Munich. I have two funny and cute sons with whom I'm living in the wonderful Munich neighbourhood Haidhausen. And I have a wonderful girlfriend.
I like my many friends, lakes, our sommer house in Sweden, trains, climbing trees, traveling, football (playing and watching) other sports (playing), music (listening live and non-live and I'm singing in a choir), literature, cayaking, good food of all kinds and a lot of other things.
Life is easy and fantastic. All it takes is being open and friendly and that's one of the easiest things to do.

host_about:
Hi there!  I have been a traveller / backpacker myself for many, many years-- and still are.
Therefore I know what is important for you as a traveller: a clean and safe neighborhood, a nice room with comfortable beds, easy and cheap transportation to the city centre or the major attractions...  and of course:  free Internet ;) 
As a host I can and want to provide you that. Our rooms are clean, spacious and lockable. Everyone gets a room and a house key, the area is silent and beautiful. No traffic, no sirens, no noise, .. just what you need for a recharching, quiet night. And in the morning:  free coffee (or tea ;) !

Well...  I am an easy to handle person who likes to travel the world. If you need something, maybe just some information-- I am happy to help you. 
As a host I want you to feel welcome and leave with a nice impression of Munich, Bavaria, Germany and it´s people...    

I´m sure you gonna like it...  ;)

name: MUNICH suburb, 3 separate rooms for up to 6 people
description:
Hi. I live in a house in Munich and in this house I have 3 rooms for rent.

This offer is good for group bookings for 4-6 People, fairs, etc.

Please note: not the complete house itself is for rent, only the 3 private / lockable rooms in the upper floor are for rent, with a shared use (with me) of the livingroom and kitchen. Quiet neigborhood, very nice area, silent, secure and welcoming.
Supermarket nearby, fresh stuff and inexpensive.
Also there is a nice Lake nearby for walking and swimming.

host_about:
Hi there!  I have been a traveller / backpacker myself for many, many years-- and still are.
Therefore I know what is important for you as a traveller: a clean and safe neighborhood, a nice room with comfortable beds, easy and cheap transportation to the city centre or the major attractions...  and of course:  free Internet ;) 
As a host I can and want to provide you that. Our rooms are clean, spacious and lockable. Everyone gets a room and a house key, the area is silent and beautiful. No traffic, no sirens, no noise, .. just what you need for a recharching, quiet night. And in the morning:  free coffee (or tea ;) !
And of course:  free Internet!

Well...  I am an easy to handle person who likes to travel the world. If you need something, maybe just some information-- I am happy to help you. 
As a host I want you to feel welcome and leave with a nice impression of Munich, Bavaria, Germany and it´s people...    

I´m sure you gonna like it...  ;)

host_about:
I am a german travelwriter and therefore spend much of my time in hotels all over the world which is a little boring after a while. They all look the same and sometimes you wake up and do not know in which city you are.

I have written a lot a travel guide and coffee table books about remote areas. I like to meet people all over the world.I live in München and at the Starnberger See in Bavaria. As a passionate book lover I am quite bad with internet and social media ;-((

The house is situated in a quiet and secure residential area, 15min walk south of westpark. In the neighborhood there are plenty of restaurants, cafés and shops.
In 2 min walking distance from the house there is a bakery with terrace where you can also have breakfast. A fruit shop, a butchery (Bavarian sausage specialties) with lunch offers and a cheese shop are nearby.
For walking or sports activities the south park (8min walk) and the west park (15min walk) are perfect. The westpark is special because of its garden and lakescape, a beer garden and a restaurant. In summer (June 3rd - September 6th) there is also a popular open air cinema.

description: Here, the world of art is combined with high living comfort. Transient rooms, sliding and mirror walls make sleeping and enjoying in the 103m² studio to be an experience. host_about:
Auf unserern Reisen hat Georg Weiss und ich herzliche Gastfreundschaft erlebt. Ich möchte diese Freude an meine Gäste weitergeben, sie persönlich Willkommen heißen und mit Ihnen, sofern sie es wollen, näher in Kontakt kommen. In jedem Fall werde ich für sie ständig telefonisch zu erreichen sein.
Zu meiner Person:
Ich habe in Wien Angewandte Kunst, Design-Mode studiert. Ich war, und bin  Anhängerin von Modern Jazz und zeitgenössischer ernster Musik. Dadurch und durch einen Zufall habe ich den Künstler Georg Weiss kennen gelernt , der in Wien an der Akademie der Bildenden Künste studiert hatte. Aus der Faszination an seiner Person und zu seiner Welt wurde eine  mehr als 45 Jahre dauernde Lebensgemeinschaft in der ich auch seine  Assistentin war.  Ich freue mich, dass sich meine Gäste im Atelier, in dem gesamte Ambiente, über 100m², wohl fühlen. "Artist´s Creative Residence" ist ein großzügiger und angenehmer Ausgagngspunkt, München zu erkunden und zu genießen, und ein wohltuender Ort, um danach Ruhe und Erholung zu finden.
Was wichtig ist für mich:
Achtung... Zuwendung... Fairness... Ehrlichkeit... Zuverlässigkeit 
"Body andt Soul"
 Kultur Kunst Wissenschaft Freiheit 
 "Teilen macht reich"
" I had a dream...."

description:

neighborhood_overview:

Our EFH is located in a predominantly green residential area with a mix of old EFH and new buildings. Ideally connected to the public transport network, 3 stops by bus, which stops opposite, to the East Railway Station. U2 and U7/8, S3 and S7 railway stations within walking distance. host_about:
Hallo, ich bin Sabine
Ich freue mich  über reiselustige, interessante Leute, die einen Stopp oder auch längeren Aufenthalt in der Dachgeschoßwohnung meines Hauses machen wollen. Wir wohnen am Rand der Innenstadt, dennoch ist es recht grün um unser Haus und von der Wohnung schaut man in hübsche Gärten mit vielen alten Bäumen. Zu Fuß bist du in 30 Minuten in der Altstadt, mit dem Rad in 10, öffentliche Verkehrsmittel sind auch in Fußnähe, du bist hier also sehr gut vernetzt. Als echtes Müncher Kindl kenne ich mich gut aus in dieser Stadt, gern gebe ich Euch ein paar Tipps. 
Ich arbeite als Lektorin und Texterin und würde mich selbst als "Kultur- und Genussmenschen" beschreiben. Ich mag es, wenn etwas ästhetisch und gepflegt ist, ich liebe Musik, Hunde (obwohl wir eine Katze haben - die Arme!), moderne Kunst, die Natur, Stille. Wenn ich selbst reise, lasse ich mit gern ohne großen Plan treiben, ich gehe aus der Türe und nehme den Weg, der mir am besten gefällt.  Zur Not habe ich einen Reiseführer in der Tasche. Was ich nicht mag: Menschenmassen, laute Geräusche, Volkstümelei, Übervorteilung.

name: ※Heart of Munich※3BR※2Min Walk to Central Station※
description:
This unique accommodation is located in the heart of Munich in the famous Schillerstraße.

Perfect for groups (e.g. bachelor/stag/hen parties, groups of friends or company groups)
Large accommodation with 3 bedrooms, 2 showers, 2 toilets, 4 washbasins
Marienplatz, Main station, Oktoberfest all within walking distance
neighborhood_overview:
This apartment is located in the middle of the famous Schillerstraße, directly at Munich Central Station. You won't find a more central location in Munich: The main station, Marienplatz, Karlsplatz-Stachus, Sendlinger Tor, the Oktoberfest and all other important hotspots are only a few minutes' walk away.

Of course, this is accompanied by a certain bustle and lively hustle of the city. Many different cultures, nationalities and people with different backgrounds live together here. It is a mix of high-class restaurants, 4-5 star hotels, bars, the German Theatre and, on the other side, shisha cafés, casinos, table dance bars and Far Eastern shops. But we must not forget that Munich itself and this area in particular are among the safest places in Europe.

However, people who are not used to such a mix might feel a bit overwhelmed at first. We would therefore ask those people who feel uncomfortable with the presence of table dance bars or casinos in the immediate vic
host_about:
My name is Thomas. I'm living in Munich for more than 10 years now. After finishing my M.Sc. in Entrepreneurship here, I founded an agency managing some flats in Munich.
My small team and I are open-minded and we love to meet new people from different areas all around the world. We want to make our guests feel like a real Bavarian here in Munich.

name: Central Oktoberfest apartment, beautiful view
description: Our spacious and fully equipped 2 room apartment is located in a prime location in Schwabing! Relax on the spacious balcony or enjoy the surroundings in the Luitpoldpark. The Oktoberfest is only about 15 minutes away. The transport links by bus, streetcar and subway allow you to explore the city without any problems.  With a comfortable bed and a sofa bed, the apartment offers enough space for up to 4 people, if needed we can provide 2 additional mattresses.
neighborhood_overview:
Our apartment is located directly at the Luitpoldpark, the perfect place to escape from everyday life and enjoy the fresh air. Whether you want to jog, go for a walk or explore the numerous playgrounds with your children, the Luitpoldpark offers something for everyone. In winter, the park offers Munich's most popular and fastest sledding hill!

Just a 10-minute walk away is the well-known Olympiapark, which serves as a venue for numerous events and activities.

Culture and car enthusiasts will appreciate the nearby BMW Museum, which is also just 10 minutes away and offers a fascinating insight into the history and innovations of the automotive industry.

In the summer months, a picturesque beer garden just 5 minutes from our apartment invites you to socialize over cool drinks and hearty Bavarian specialties.

Experience Munich's charm and diversity in our beautiful and attractive apartment, which serves as the perfect base for all your adventure
host_about: Hi, we are Valentin and Iris. We are both living in this apartment if we are not on vacation :) We like to cook with our friends in our apartment. Furthermore, we are traveling a lot and that is the reason why we sometimes rent out our apartment. Hopefully you like our apartment the same as we do!

We’re the favourite choice for the backpacker on a budget, the student with some study-abroad holidays to burn, the gap year gapper looking to do something outrageous, the solo traveller searching for travel buddies, soul mates, or just somebody to have a (lot of) laughs with, or the group looking to travel with an even bigger group of absolute legends.
Our Stokies want the most affordable experiences at the world’s wildest, most popular and craziest festivals and destinations with an authentic feel, a flexible schedule and options to suit your budget. neighborhood_overview:
The unique location in the heart of Munich makes this apartment the perfect base for discovery tours in the Bavarian metropolis. You reach any attraction in the bustling city center in a few minutes. At the same time you enjoy peace and quiet in the luxurious environment of your accommodation. The pedestrian area with the Isartor and the Viktualienmarkt is just a few steps away. In the pedestrian zone you will find practically everything your heart desires - from beer mugs with salt glaze to the products of world-famous luxury brands. In the Gärtnerplatz- and Glockenbachviertel, you can discover workshops of artisans. The offer ranges from traditional Bavarian jewelry to the original clothes from independent labels.

name: Families welcome: big, sunny flat in Munich center
description: Our home is in a a newly-built apartment block in Haidhausen, just 10 minutes from the city center. The interior is a mixture of  modern design and flea market objects in a cozy atmosphere. The view is green with plenty of old trees in a park with a large meadow and  a huge playground. The Isar river is just a few minutes away. The subway station is five minutes by foot and there are several bus stations reachable within one minute.
neighborhood_overview:
Haidhausen is a 19th century city extension on the right river banks of the Isar. In the last 20 years it has become a fashionable urban district known for its charming streets lined with colorful buildings, little cafes, a wide range of restaurants, shops selling hand-crafted design and fashion, while still being very family-friendly.

One of the most popular spots in Haidhausen is the Wiener Platz, a bustling square surrounded by cafes, shops, and a local market. It's a great place to grab a coffee and people-watch, or pick up some fresh produce and local specialties.

neighborhood_overview:
This apartment is in a quiet green neighbourhood, but very well connected to various public transports and to major freeways and Autobahns. Transportation to the very city center and to fabulous Schwabing night life is less than 20 min by public transport around the clock.
You also can enjoy one of the most beautiful and traditional beergardens in Munich, 5 min on foot away. There are restaurants, deli shops, supermarkets, bakery, butcher from 50 meters to 200 meters away.
Don't miss Westpark with its fabulous Asian gardens and temples, about 10 min away on bus.
For a city hustling and bustling time-out enjoy river Isar around Flaucher jetty with its wild creeks and islands and beergarden and river shore to relax and have fun, especially in summer. Tierpark Hellabrunn animal park is worth seeing and close by. All that is within 15 min by public transport.

Lean back and feel welcome!

description:
Our cozy apartment for 4-6 guests is in the center of Munich, only minutes walking distance to Maximilianstraße & Marienplatz, the Old Town and exclusive boutiques. name: Big bright house,5rms,yard,sauna,gym,metro,parking
description:
Rent a complete, large and light-flooded wellness house (5 rooms, 3 bathrooms) with a special conservatory, sauna, private garden, private parking, comfort workplaces and fitness/games room in the beautiful south of Munich directly on the subway (suitable for 1 or 2 families).
Perfect location:
- 1 min. walk to the subway (line U3: 15 min. to Marienplatz, 20 min. to the English Garden, 5 min. to the zoo/Isar)
- short drive to Lake Starnberg (location on the A95-15 min.)
neighborhood_overview:
Our neighborhood is perfect for families:
- the house is in a cul-de-sac in a quiet play street. Most cars run slowly. This is also a good skateboard or scooter, etc.
- in the immediate vicinity there are shops, supermarkets, restaurants, cafes, a swimming pool, bowling center and a library within walking distance.
- at the end of the street is directly the subway station, which takes you to the Olympic center without changing trains (also to the Theresienwiese, the English Garden, Sendlinger Tor, Marienplatz, Thalkirchen/Zoo/Isar)
- right next to our street begins a large park, perfect for jogging, cycling, walking, etc. through which you can get to the Südpark and even further
- the house is close to the Kare Kraftwerk (furnishing house and rooftop restaurant)
- The A95 highway is very close
- Forstenrieder Park (e.g. with beer garden Forst Kasten) is also very close.
host_about:

name: Gesamtes Sonniges Loft direkt an der Isar
description:
Our apartment is located in the beautiful district of Au-Haidhausen just a few steps from the Isar. On the opposite bank is the lively Glockenbachviertel with many bars, restaurants, cafes and numerous small shops.
You can walk to the Isar in a few minutes. Here you can lie in the sun in fine weather, swim or keep your feet in the water in the evening with a wine on the shore. Many of the sights are also within walking distance.
neighborhood_overview: Our apartment is located in a quiet location directly on the Isar and in the immediate vicinity of Mariahilfplatz. A small farmers' market takes place twice a week at Mariahilfplatz. Numerous beer gardens, such as the beautiful Paulaner Biergarten am Nockerberg, are within walking distance. Right across the Isar River, the lively Glockenbach district with its beautiful gardener's square, many restaurants, cafes and bars, as well as small shops are a 5-minute walk away. The beautiful Isar invites you to sunbathe, swim and drink wine. The highway is easily accessible, so you can be in the mountains in 30-60 minutes.

neighborhood_overview:
Royal squares, magnificent buildings and parks: Schwabing-West in Munich
The district of the squares – maybe that's the best way to describe Schwabing-West. Because with the Kurfürstenplatz, the Hohenzollernplatz or the Elisabethplatz are some of the most famous Munich squares in this district. And with the Luitpoldpark, the district also has a relaxed green area with a view. We'll tell you what makes the district of Schwabing-West.

Shopping: Hohenzollernstraße and Elisabethmarkt

On Hohenzollernstraße, typical Schwabinger life is bustling. Between Kurfürstenplatz and Leopoldstraße go shopping for those Munichers who are too crowded or mainstream in the pedestrian zone. This is where a small fashion boutique lines up with other international labels, decorative shops and antiques in backyards with small street cafés and restaurants - and in the small side streets you can discover beautiful Art Nouveau buildings. host_about: Welcome to my Airbnb profile! I'm a professional tour guide originally from Munich, now residing in beautiful Dublin where the Guinness flows like a river and the accents are thicker than a bowl of Irish stew. I have a passion for travel and have been fortunate enough to see many amazing places around the world, from the Great Wall of China to the Great Wall of Pizza in New York City. As a fluent speaker of English, Spanish, Danish, and German, I'm able to connect with guests from all over the globe, but I'll still need a translator for my grandma's cooking instructions. I love being a host on Airbnb and look forward to welcoming you to my home, sharing my knowledge of the local area with you and maybe even teaching you how to properly drink a pint of Guinness.

neighborhood_overview:
First mentioned in official records from around the year 808, Haidhausen is significantly older than the core of Munich. Along with the neighbouring district of Au, it was one of Munich’s suburbs for a long time until it was incorporated into the city middle of the 19th century.

Outside the heart of the old town, on the right-hand side of the Isar, the district once provided a home to day labourers, foreign guest workers and recent arrivals from the countryside. For hundreds of years, they earned their daily bread by quarrying gravel and clay. Drawing on the power of the Isar River and its subsidiaries, craftsmen settled along the water, setting up tanneries and fishing companies.

Many Haidhausers find themselves constantly drawn back to the neighbourhood where everyone knows and greets each other. Twice a year, the residents of Haidhausen invite visitors into their courtyards for flea markets. These provide visitors with the ideal opportunity to gain a rare glimp

name: 3Room + 2Bath Apt + Breakfast in Center of Munich
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment in centrally located in the Maxvorstadt neighborhood. Maxvorstadt is directly next to the historic old town. Odeonsplatz is 10min by foot, famous Marienplatz is 15 mins by foot.

Nearby, you will find Maxvorstadt's many streets filled with hip restaurants and cafes. As both big universities of Munich are located in Maxvorstadt, the area radiates a young and international vibe.

Also, Maxvorstadt features Munich's most renowned museums such as the 3 Pinakotheken for medieval, 19-20th century and modern art, the Neue Sammlung for industrial design, and the new NS-Dokumentationszentrum that explains the controversial role of Munich during WWII.

All are in a short walking distance from the apartment, and I am happy to suggest you more hidden places based on your interests.

name: Beautiful flat in Haidhausen
description:
Quiet and perfectly located flat. 3 min walking distance to Ostbahnhof. Door to door 15 minutes direct line to the Oktoberfest .
Two bedrooms apartment with one queen size bed, one sofa bed for two, one single bed and an extra mat if needed.
You can use the bathtub and relax on the balcony. There is washing machine, a small dishwasher, high spend internet, and everything you need except aTV.
The neighborhood is wonderful. Easy access everywhere very shortly. Food shopping amenities until 11pm.
neighborhood_overview:
You will find a large choice of restaurants and coffee places : right in front is Claude et Julien, a small French bakery, downstairs is Saigon Delhi, a good Vietnamese restaurant. If you want to eat Vegan cuisine you can go to iunu or if you need to eat on the way, "Nana eat and run" makes delicious falafel and israeli cuisine. There is also a wonderful but very small cocktail bar called barroom by walking distance and Mezzodi if you want to enjoy good wine sitting outside. You have two discount supermarkets around Ostbahnhof (Aldi and Liddl) and a DM (droguerie). If you'd like to have bio and more fresh products, you can walk 7-8 minutes to Alnatura.
On Sundays the supermarkets Edeka and the DM underground are open in Ostbahnhof.

There is a playground 150m away from the flat (Hypopark).

If you want more tips about restaurants in the city, don't hesitate to ask me, as I'm a bit of a foodie.

name: Helle, grosse, zentrale Wohnung mit Balkon
description:
From this apartment you can see all the way to Munich Cathedral and the Olympic Tower! ✨

You are right in the middle of it - super fast in the city and very close to the lively district of Giesing with restaurants and all shopping facilities.

At the same time you are on the fourth floor (no
Elevator!) removed from the hustle and bustle of everyday life.

The nearby Isar beach offers the most beautiful nature and miles of walking paths……🌞

This place is warm, has plenty of space.
neighborhood_overview:
The neighborhood of Giesing, in which the apartment is located, offers a lot: Just around the corner is the newly trendy brewery "Giesinger Bräu" in Munich with a Bräustüberl and the famous Nockherberg with its Paulan beer garden.

There are old craftsmen's cottages and the very beautiful "Giesinger Dom", the Holy Cross Church. The Martin Luther Church is almost right in front of the house.

The headquarters / training facilities of FC Bayern Munich and from 1860 Munich are about 15 minutes away.

With tram 25, which starts at my place in front of the house, you get to
Green forest with a castle / museum and the BAVARIA film studio where you can make the popular movie tour.
host_about:
Reisen und Unterwegs-sein ist für mich nicht nur ein Vergnügen, sondern auch Quelle meiner Kreativität. Ich liebe es, die Welt zu erforschen!

Auch meine Heimatstadt München ist für mich stets eine Quelle von Inspiration! Hier bin ich immer wieder ein entdeckender Reisender, wenn ich z.B. oft mit dem Fahrrad unterwegs bin. Oder mich einfach an der Isar „hinchille“. 

Airbnb hab ich als zuverlässige und hochprofessionelle  Plattform kennenlernen dürfen und ich freue mich sehr, nun auch Gastgeber zu sein! 

Ich freue mich auf deinen Besuch!

For max. 5 adults (+possibly thermarest for kids) in the side street of Munich city center (Süd-Haidhausen).

On foot 3 minutes to bus, bakery with snack bar, Rewe, 7 minutes to S-Bahn and Großmarkt, 10 minutes to the subway.

1 bedroom (13 sqm) with 2 single beds, 1 living/sleeping room (17.8 sqm) with 1 bed + 1 comfortable sofa bed (140 cm) and pantry kitchen, bathroom with separate toilet.

In our area of the side street, there are predominantly two-storey single and apartment buildings with large gardens and about 50 meters away is the first park with playground. The nearest two parks with playgrounds are about a 6-8 minute walk.

In Munich, in addition to many museums, there is also an old Art Nouveau swimming pool and an Art Nouveau sauna in it. This is the Müllersche Volksbad.

For smaller children, a department in the lower floor of the Deutsches Museum is particularly suitable and for school children the museum "Mensch und Natur" in the right side wing of the castle "Nymphenburg". To the left of the castle with its castle park is the botanical garden. You can also drive there easily by car, because there is a lot of parking options there.

neighborhood_overview:
Haidhausen is a 19th century city extension on the right river banks of the Isar. In the last 20 years it has become a fashionable urban district known for its charming streets lined with colorful buildings, little cafes, a wide range of restaurants, shops selling hand-crafted design and fashion, while still being very family-friendly.

One of the most popular spots in Haidhausen is the Wiener Platz, a bustling square surrounded by cafes, shops, and a local market. It's a great place to grab a coffee and people-watch, or pick up some fresh produce and local specialties.

neighborhood_overview:
This apartment is located in the middle of the famous Schillerstraße, right next to Munich Central Station. You won't find a more central location in Munich: The main train station, Marienplatz, Karlsplatz-Stachus, Sendlinger Tor, the Oktoberfest and all other important hotspots are just a few minutes' walk away.

Of course, this also brings with it a certain amount of hustle and bustle and lively city life. Many different cultures, nationalities and people from different backgrounds live together here. It is a mix of high-class restaurants, 4-5 star hotels, bars, the German Theater and, on the other hand, shisha cafés, casinos, table dance bars and Far Eastern stores. However, it should not be forgotten that Munich itself and this area in particular is one of the safest places in Europe.

However, people who are not used to such a mix may feel a little overwhelmed at first. We would therefore ask people who feel uncomfortable with the presence of table dance bars o
host_about:
My name is Thomas. I'm living in Munich for more than 10 years now. After finishing my M.Sc. in Entrepreneurship here, I founded an agency managing some flats in Munich.
My small team and I are open-minded and we love to meet new people from different areas all around the world. We want to make our guests feel like a real Bavarian here in Munich.

Munich, especially the Maxvorstadt district, is undoubtedly one of the most popular areas in the Isar metropolis. Despite its central location, the area boasts numerous green spaces and parks, including the English Garden, one of the world's largest urban parks, the Hirschgarten, and the picturesque Nymphenburg Palace Park. Public transportation is easily accessible on foot, making it convenient to reach the city's major attractions.
This neighborhood is an excellent choice for travelers looking to experience the authentic Munich lifestyle.

host_about:
German (English description is further down):
Meine Freunde nennen mich eine Frohnatur. Ich liebe das Reisen. Es ist immer toll, eine neue Stadt oder ein neues Land mit anderen Menschen kennenlernen zu dürfen. Es öffnet sehr die Einstellung zum Leben. So ist für mich Rassismus unverständlich. Ich bin pazifistisch eingestellt, denn Konflikte kann man immer mit Diplomatie lösen.
Neben meinem Beruf bin ich sozial engagiert als Judotrainer und als Freiwilliger für Stammzellentransporte von Leukämiepatienten.
In der Freizeit gehe ich gerne wandern, Rad fahren, schwimmen und mache Judo. Gerne würde ich wieder mehr Basketball spielen.
Beruflich bin ich Softwareingenieur und programmiere sehr gerne Handelssysteme in der Programmiersprache Java.

English:
My friends call me a cheerful nature. I love to travel. It is always amazing to visit a new city or a new country. It is also great getting known other people there. It opens the point of view to life a lot. Therefore I do not like racism. I am pacifistic; conflicts can be always solved diplomatically. Beside my job I am engaged as a Judo coach and I am volunteering for stem cell transports for leukaemia patients.
In my free time I like hiking, cycling, swimming and Judo. I also would like to play more Basketball again.
My job is software engineering, so I program automatic trading systems in the programming language Java.
